SAR represents the relative activity of Na+ in soil exchange reactions and is used to evaluate the degree of alkalization of irrigation water (Ayers and Westcot 1985). Irrigation with high-SAR water can cause soil slabs. The formula is as follows:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
